{
  "analysis": "The current background fastText training (PID 4251) with character n-grams is too slow: ETA over an hour and likely to produce a huge model. The terminal is occupied by an active polling loop, so I need to interrupt it before doing anything else. Previous autotune failed to produce a final model and had best F1 only 0.5994, in part because loss was manually fixed. The best next strategy is to kill the slow job, clean up artifacts, verify the existing autotune split files, and run a clean unrestricted autotune with only the size constraint, f1 metric, and 900s duration. Later I will evaluate the produced model and copy it to `/app/model.bin` if it meets accuracy/size.",
  "plan": "1. Send Ctrl+C to stop the current polling loop.\n2. Kill PID 4251 if still running, using SIGKILL if needed.\n3. Verify no fastText process remains.\n4. Clean up char-ngram artifacts and previous autotune artifacts.\n5. Verify `/app/work/train_aut.txt` and `/app/work/val_aut.txt` line counts.\n6. Start a clean background fastText autotune job with no manually fixed loss/hyperparameters, only autotune validation/metric/duration/modelsize and thread count.\n7. Poll for a bounded period to confirm it started and monitor progress.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "C-c\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "pid=$(cat /app/work/train_char.pid 2>/dev/null || true); echo \"pid=$pid\"; if [ -n \"$pid\" ] && [ -d \"/proc/$pid\" ]; then kill -INT \"$pid\" 2>/dev/null || true; sleep 2; if [ -d \"/proc/$pid\" ]; then kill -KILL \"$pid\" 2>/dev/null || true; fi; echo 'killed'; else echo 'not running'; fi\n",
      "duration": 5.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "grep -l 'fasttext' /proc/*/comm 2>/dev/null | head -5 || echo 'no fasttext procs'\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "rm -f /app/work/model_char.bin /app/work/model_char.vec /app/work/model_char.ftz /app/work/train_char.log /app/work/train_char.pid /app/work/model_aut.bin /app/work/model_aut.vec /app/work/model_aut.ftz /app/work/autotune.log /app/work/autotune.pid /app/work/autotune2.log /app/work/autotune2.pid /app/work/model_aut2.bin /app/work/model_aut2.vec /app/work/model_aut2.ftz\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "wc -l /app/work/train_aut.txt /app/work/val_aut.txt /app/work/train.txt /app/work/test.txt\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "nohup /opt/fastText/fasttext supervised -input /app/work/train_aut.txt -output /app/work/model_aut2 -autotune-validation /app/work/val_aut.txt -autotune-metric f1 -autotune-duration 900 -autotune-modelsize 140000000 -thread $(nproc) > /app/work/autotune2.log 2>&1 &\necho $! > /app/work/autotune2.pid\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "for i in $(seq 1 10); do\n  pid=$(cat /app/work/autotune2.pid 2>/dev/null || true)\n  if [ -n \"$pid\" ] && [ -d \"/proc/$pid\" ]; then status=running; else status=finished; fi\n  size=$(stat -c %s /app/work/model_aut2.bin 2>/dev/null || echo 0)\n  printf 'iter=%s status=%s bin_size=%s ' \"$i\" \"$status\" \"$size\"\n  tail -1 /app/work/autotune2.log 2>/dev/null || true\n  if [ \"$status\" = finished ] && [ \"$size\" -gt 0 ]; then echo 'autotune2_done_break'; break; fi\n  sleep 30\ndone\n",
      "duration": 330.0
    }
  ]
}
